26/03/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer said on Friday (March 23rd) that Albania and other aspirants in the region have concrete prospects of joining the Alliance, if they accomplish the necessary reforms. 
During talks in Brussels with Albanian Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu, de Hoop Scheffer welcomed efforts made by Tirana to restructure its armed forces and fight corruption and organised crime. 
He stressed that this would be an important year for the entire Balkan region, especially in the light of the Kosovo status settlement process. 
(Albanian News, KohaJone, Shekulli - 26/03/07)
